metadata.name: Cosmic Type #27
metadata.description:
Cosmic Type is a kinetic type experiment that explores both graphic space as structural and semantic agency. Inspired by the early pioneering work of the concrete poets such as Dom Sylvester Hou√©dard, Ian Hamilton Finley and Steve McCaffe, the project is a play with letters, words and graphic form in the computational and generative space.

Each iteration gives you the possibility to discover a variety of visual form through exploring the system. Please explore your iteration with the key interactions below. It is hoped that you give the time to explore and observe. If you don't, you may end up with just a blank canvas. 

Thank you for collecting. 

Key Interactions

‚Äòa‚Äô activates forward motion on/off
‚Äòb‚Äô activates backward motion on/off
‚Äòr‚Äô rotates grid 45¬∞ [ rotates on key pressed]
‚Äòf‚Äô rotates the grid freely [ stops on key release ]
‚Äòp‚Äô switches grid scale on/off [ this can be CPU heavy on older machines ] 
‚Äòg‚Äô extra glyphs on/off
‚Äòq‚Äô return to the initial state 


Program written by Mark Webster

metadata.name: Pobbles #64
metadata.description:
The pobbles are generative blob-rocks: staring in silence, sometimes half-smiling, generally bored. 

‚Ä¢ The pobbles are digital recreations of a series of rock-doodles by S.F.Kislev (my big brother). They are an attempt to capture a specific, singular handwriting, and evolve it using code. 
‚Ä¢ See the original, 2014 handmade version here - https://pobbles.tez.page..
‚Ä¢ Alternative titles considered include Peggles‚Ñ¢, Plops‚Ñ¢, Blobbies‚Ñ¢, Floofs‚Ñ¢, Flintstones‚Ñ¢, Lardies‚Ñ¢, Plumps‚Ñ¢, Fats‚Ñ¢ and Wet-Ones‚Ñ¢. 
‚Ä¢ The pobbles are written entirely in paper.js and p5.js. 
‚Ä¢ The pobbles are an effort to take generative art into the realm of the cute. 
‚Ä¢ They work well with toddlers.

metadata.name: Serene Garden #65
metadata.description:
A Serene Garden is a peaceful and tranquil outdoor space designed to evoke feelings of calm and relaxation.

The overall design and atmosphere of a Serene Garden encourage reflection and contemplation, making it a peaceful retreat from the hustle and bustle of daily life. It's a place where visitors can slow down, breathe deeply, and reconnect with nature. Whether through the gentle sound of a fountain, the fragrance of blooming flowers, or the rustle of leaves in the wind, a serene garden provides a sensory escape that soothes the mind and nourishes the soul.

As a features, there are 17 color palettes for flowers, beautifull handpicked gradient backgounds whitch are mixing with flower palettes and together gives pleasing expirience of render/output.

To download high quality image, open 'Live' and press "S" to save 2500x1800px



February 2023
Made with P5js

metadata.name: VIBE #97
VIBE #99
Emotional Shell #71
metadata.description:
Manual Dutch Auction (DA): 72 ¬∑ 54 ¬∑ 40 ¬∑ 30 ¬∑ 24 ¬∑ 20 every 8 minutes.
Auction will stop changing price when non-reserves are fully minted, and then drop one price tier.

---------

The feeling of being human ‚Äì with all of its intricate hopes, struggles, and fleeting emotions ‚Äì seems so unique that we assume artificial intelligence could never replicate our experience. And while we devise systems for solving unfathomably complex problems, generating algorithmic creativity, and unlocking regenerative biological possibilities, we simultaneously cling to the power and originality of emotional feeling ‚Äì believing it to be the irreplaceable source of what makes us human.

If the body is our shell for emotion and soul, can an artificial humanoid be another vessel for these thoughts and feelings ‚Äì for human essence itself? If our ‚Äòsoul‚Äô is the last stand between us and the machines, what happens when the soul becomes transferable? That we may see answers to these questions looks more real every year, and is perhaps a little frightening. 

Emotional Shell uses introspective portraits of future selves to question what it means to be human, when the people around us are no longer human.

---------

Warning: This piece is GPU intensive, it may not render on lower end devices.

Press 1-3 to select from low, medium, and high quality settings
Press 'S' to save the image at the current scale
Press 'H' to save the image at 2400px resolution

metadata.name: Petal 3D #5
metadata.description:
This project features an abstract, multi-layered structure that resembles a blooming flower or organic shape. The composition is characterized by overlapping translucent forms that create a sense of depth and fluidity. The colors blend seamlessly, adding to the ethereal and dynamic quality. The use of gradients and transparency enhances the three-dimensional effect, giving the piece an almost holographic nature, a fusion of organic and mathematical aesthetics.

Made of five constant height bands perpendicular to the surface of a sphere. Position, RGB values and transparency of the bands are governed by the control points of closed loop Bezier curves.

Press [1/2/4] to redraw at 800/1600/3200 px resolution.
Press [s] to save a png at the current resolution.

100% code-generated artwork, written in javascript using the p5.js library.

AndersB 2025

metadata.name: Spring flowers #N #1
metadata.description:
‚ÄúSpring flowers‚Äù is a generative art series conceived in Kyiv in March 2025, under the tender influence of the city‚Äôs blooming spring. This work captures the delicate essence of renewal and the vibrant pulse of nature awakening, drawing inspiration from Andy Warhol‚Äôs iconic Flowers series. Like Warhol‚Äôs bold yet playful exploration of floral forms, this series reimagines blossoms through a digital lens, infusing them with a soft, watercolor effect that evokes the gentle breath of spring in Kyiv.

Each piece unfolds as a unique composition of five abstract flowers, their petals painted with fluid, translucent hues‚Äîvibrant corals, sunny yellows, serene blues, and lush greens‚Äîset against a subtle, pastel background. The black centers of the flowers, fading into airy grays, mimic the organic diffusion of watercolor on paper, while animated particles drift across the canvas, embodying the breeze that carries spring‚Äôs promise. This interplay of stillness and motion reflects the harmony of nature‚Äôs cycles, blending algorithmic precision with the spontaneity of hand-painted art.

Why Collect?
Unique Generative Creations: Every artwork is algorithmically distinct, offering collectors an exclusive piece of digital flora.

*Warholian Echoes: A modern nod to Andy Warhol‚Äôs Flowers, merging pop art legacy with cutting-edge generative techniques.
*Kyiv‚Äôs Spring Spirit: Created amidst Kyiv‚Äôs blossoming season, it encapsulates a moment of beauty and resilience.
*Own a piece of ‚ÄúSpring flowers‚Äù  ‚Äî a celebration of spring‚Äôs fleeting magic, rooted in Kyiv‚Äôs vibrant soul and the timeless allure of watercolor blooms.

***
Press S or double-click to save as PNG.

***

Kyiv, 17.03.2025
